<s> One note: as long as the cache-validator of an object remains the same it is OK for copies of it to persist in the cache under separate keys, even though it may be the result of content-negotiation in several ways, or the result of a direct request.  </s>
<s> (Example: you have URLs A, B, and C. Requests for both A and B yield "location" C, as do direct requests for C. Though each request would result in a different (key,object) in the cache, ((A,C), (B,C), and (C,-)), if the cache validator for C is the same in all cases there is no problem leaving the other copies in the cache.  </s>
<s> The only performance hit occurs when C changes.  </s>
<s> Then the next similar request for A, B, or C must flush all other occurrences of C from the cache.  </s>
<s> So it really isn't so bad.) Never-the-less, I believe this is the route that will have to be taken.  </s>
